          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1715609700282-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop your<strong> brown onion[s] </strong>into thick discs (roughly 1cm thick), then pop out the centres so that you have different sized discs</p><p>Add the <strong>onion discs </strong>to a bowl with a handful of <strong>flour</strong> and give everything a good mix up until fully coated – this is your <strong>floured onion</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>cornflour</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>in a small bowl with 45ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[70ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[90ml] </span><strong>water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your<strong> batter</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
