    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once the pan is hot, reduce the heat to medium-high, then dip the<strong> floured onion</strong> into the <strong>batter</strong> and turn several times until fully coated</p><p>Add the <strong>coated onion </strong>to the pan and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until cooked through, golden and crispy – these are your <strong>onion rings</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
